args:
Annelie and friends had been planning to make
an appearance at a circus festival, but due to
a rival troupe poaching all their people,
they're suffering a shortage. Learning this,
the party joins the troupe as its newest
members and resolves to help them out.
I can hardly believe we'll be able to put\non our show in such a FANCY location!
You can't just go around kissing people\nwhenever you damn well please!
Why are you being a wet blanket, Fritz?\nIt was just a thank-you peck on the cheek.
Call it a peck or a smooch or whatever\nyou like—he's STILL turning red!
*sigh* We seriously need to do something\nabout your excessive friendliness.
N-no, it's fine! I'm glad you're so...happy.
Anyway, I think we got the tent up, so what\ndo you say we show it to everyone?
It's time to put on a show and give\npeople a day to remember!
...And with that, today's performance is\nat an end! Thank you one and all for\nbeing such a wonderful audience!
Great work on the show, Annelie!
It feels as if the whole atmosphere\nof the castle has changed.
You guys should stay here FOREVER!
I could spend the rest of my life\ninside this big sparkly tent!
Heh. Then perhaps we'll leave one here.
That way we could come back and perform\nat any time.
And we'd be delighted to have a second\nplace to call home!
That said, a small tent like this limits\nthe number of acts we can perform.
We'd be able to do a lot more if we\nhad something bigger.
But if we win the circus festival,\nwe can DEFINITELY upsize the tent.
Well, maybe we can help with that.
I know people here would really enjoy\nbeing able to see lots of different acts.
So what do you need from us?\nWe're up for anything!
...So let's all welcome our new recruits,\n{player_name} and friends!
The prince said you were willing to\nhelp out, did he not?
Which is good, because there's no way\nwe'll win that festival with the manpower\nwe have now.
Hell, never mind winning—we wouldn't\neven be able to PARTICIPATE.
Fritz! This is not something for us to\nbe discussing with our guests!
But ma'am, if we don't make some\nchanges, we'll be kicked out of the festival.
Didn't you want to win it and get our\ntroupe back to the way it was?
Maybe you can start by explaining the\nsituation in a little more detail.
The long and short of it is this:\nWe don't have enough people for\nour troupe to compete in the festival.
We had more a while back, but...
Well, when I took over this circus from my\nfather, a rival troupe swooped in and\npoached a bunch of our talent.
All we have left are the performers\nyou see before you.
So as we've been touring, we've also\nbeen searching for new blood that\nmight be interested in joining up.
That said, we can't force people to join—\nahem, FRITZ!—so I'm sorry to have\nburdened you all with our problems.

We've no right to call ourselves
entertainers if we end a show by
revealing all of our dirty laundry
to our honored guests.
...Although I may have lost the right to\ncall myself a ringmaster when I couldn't\nkeep our people from leaving.
So if we were to join you, would you be\nable to perform at the festival?
Then we're in. We'll join your circus.
It can't be a permanent arrangement\nor anything, but I think we can spare\nsome time until the festival, at least.

This is the least we can do for all of the
excitement you spread around the castle.
We'll put all of our energy into seeing
your show is a success!
Oh, thank you all so much!
Guess it's time to figure out the acts,\nthen. We'll get to it first thing tomorrow.
...This tightrope walking activity seems to\nbe rather good practice for cultivating\none's balance.
Say, you're a natural at this!
And it don't hurt that you cut a real\npretty picture up there.
Are you LEERING at me, sir?!\nI'll not stand for—AAAAAUGH!\nI'M FAAAALLIIIIING!
Whoops! Good thing we got that net.\n...Right then! Ranzal. Juggling, is it?
Hah! Hoh! Har! ...Sure am, pal!\nAnd boy, I am NAILIN' it!
That's some impressive stuff, Ranzal.\nAre you sure you've never done this?
Oh, this is nothin'. Time to up the speed!\n...Hah! Ho! Har! Haa—OW! Dangit!\nStupid club hit me in the head!
Look at meeee! I'm a birdieeee!\nI'm flying with no tricks or wires or\nanything wheeeeeeeee!
It's not much of a trick for a faerie\nto take flight, Notte.
At any rate, this ＂trampoline＂ certainly\nfeels rather curiou—WHOA!
You're flying even higher than me!\nWheee, right? Wheeeeee!
Well, looks like all you cats have the\nspirits of true entertainers.
I've got high hopes for you newbies!
And what act are you interested in trying,\n{player_name}?
I'm not sure. They all have their charms,\nso I'm having a little trouble deciding.
In that case, why not think it over while\npracticing the fundamentals?
Hee hee! You'll see when we get there.\nCome on everyone—we're relocating!
Annelie! How exactly is slaying fiends\n＂fundamental＂ practice for the circus?!
Our role is to provide an enchanting\nperformance, yes?
Thus, it's critical for you to be aware how\neven the slightest movement holds the\npower to enchant an audience!
I've never seen a fiend dispatched with\nsuch...elegance before.
That must be what she means when she\nspeaks of understanding how we might\nenchant a potential audience.
However, I still fail to realize why we must\npractice that by slaying fiends.
Slaying fiends is sorta what you folks do\nday in and day out, right?

You all just started learning your circus
acts, so there's no way they'll be anything
but ham-fisted—and no way to make them
elegant through practice.
So instead, we'll teach you to be elegant\nby having you perform actions that are\nalready familiar.
Plus, the thrill of slaying fiends is pretty\nsimilar to the thrill of the circus.
That's crazy! Yer a crazy person!
O-okay, everyone! For now\nlet's try to act like Annelie!
